# The one module ../validation-data/deltasigma_deltasigma_test.py, run by
# ../deltasigma/deltasigma_test.ini, generates several output files. This makes
# the 'make' rule for this target extra complicated, since we don't want to
# re-run the same CosmoSIS workflow several times to generate the same set of
# files. Breaking up the giant one-liner defining the target and dependencies
# seems fragile, so if you try to do so, please test the result carefully!
../validation-data/deltasigma_xi_nfwonly.out ../validation-data/deltasigma_xi_mm_2halo.out ../validation-data/deltasigma_Sigma_nfwonly.out ../validation-data/deltasigma_Sigma_mm_2halo.out ../validation-data/deltasigma_bias.out: ../cosmosis_tests/deltasigma/deltasigma_test.py ../cosmosis_tests/deltasigma/deltasigma_test.ini ../src/modules/deltasigma/deltasigma_values.ini
	@echo "About to run cosmosis to generate $@"
	cd .. && cosmosis cosmosis_tests/deltasigma/deltasigma_test.ini > /dev/null

